	(text "CHEMIN C — TUBE HERITAGE\n\nTube 1 (V1, ECC83 #1):\n  V1a (section A): Common-cathode gain stage\n    Rp1=220K, Rk1=1.5K, Ck1=22µF/63V, Rg1=1M\n    Av ≈ -78 (37.8 dB) with cathode bypassed\n    Coupling: C3C(1µF/400V film) from Signal Rail\n\n  INTERSTAGE ATTENUATOR (Pole C of SW1):\n    V1a plate → Cc1(470nF/400V) → R_shunt to GND → Cc2(470nF/400V) → V1b grid\n    R_shunt values: 2.2K (+10dB) to 1M (+50dB)\n\n  V1b (section B): Common-cathode gain stage\n    Rp2=220K, Rk2=1.5K, Ck2=22µF/63V, Rg2=1M\n    Same gain as V1a\n\nTube 2 (V2, ECC83 #2) — White Cathode Follower:\n  V2a (section A, bottom): Cathode-follower amplifier\n    Input: V1b plate via Cc3(330nF/400V)\n    Rk_WCF=1.5K, Rg3=1M\n  V2b (section B, top): Shunt regulator\n    Rp_WCF=100K, Cg_WCF=1µF/400V (feedback from V2a plate)\n  OUTPUT: V2a cathode = V2b cathode junction\n    Zout ≈ 100-150R (WCF advantage)\n\n  Output: WCF junction → C_outC(100µF bipol + 4.7µF film) → R_outC(10R) → OUTPUT_C\n\nUse ECC83_Triode symbol from TripleTopoCustom library\n  V1 = unit 1 (V1a) + unit 2 (V1b)\n  V2 = unit 1 (V2a) + unit 2 (V2b)"
		(at 25.4 180.0 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.524 1.524)) (justify left))
		(uuid "f6000001-tube-text-0006-000000000001")
	)
)
